The paper proposes a new meta-learning algorithm for few-shot learning that extends the PAC-Bayes framework. The paper also introduces a generative-based approach to model the shared prior and the posterior of task-specific model parameters. The benchmarks used in the paper are related to classification and regression tasks, which are commonly associated with machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
